{"web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/12/05/technology/internet-firms-step-up-efforts-to-stop-spying.html", "snippet": "After surveillance by the National Security Agency, major Internet companies like Microsoft and Yahoo have moved to strengthen protections of users\u2019 data.", "lead_paragraph": "After surveillance by the National Security Agency, major Internet companies like Microsoft and Yahoo have moved to strengthen protections of users\u2019 data.", "abstract": "Major Internet companies, responding to furor over revelations of surveillance by National Security Agency, are rushing to strengthen protections of users' data by adding state-of-the-art encryption features; are trying to reassure customers that they are doing what they can to protect their data from spying, even as billions of dollars in revenue hang in the balance; Microsoft and Yahoo are latest to announce plans to shield data.", "print_page": "1", "blog": [], "source": "The New York Times", "multimedia": [{"width": 190, "url": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-thumbWide.jpg", "height": 126, "subtype": "wide", "legacy": {"wide": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-thumbWide.jpg", "wideheight": "126", "widewidth": "190"}, "type": "image"}, {"width": 600, "url": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-articleLarge.jpg", "height": 400, "subtype": "xlarge", "legacy": {"xlargewidth": "600", "xlarge": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "type": "image"}, {"width": 75, "url": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-thumbStandard.jpg", "height": 75, "subtype": "thumbnail", "legacy": {"thumbnailheight": "75", "thumbnail": "images/2013/12/05/business/Secrecy1/Secrecy1-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75"}, "type": "image"}], "headline": {"main": "Internet Firms Step Up Efforts to Stop Spying", "print_headline": "Internet Firms Step Up Efforts to Stop Spying"}, "keywords": [{"rank": "1", "is_major": "Y", "name":